1
00:00:11,933 --> 00:00:13,433
Do you know a laundrywoman?

2
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:15,500
My daughter.
That's her specialty.

3
00:00:15,567 --> 00:00:18,400
So now you will be working
as a stay-out laundrywoman.

4
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:21,233
Hey! Don't do that
to the poor bird.

5
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:22,767
Wait, where are you taking me?

6
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:23,933
Don't be noisy.

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,200
- This suits you.
- Flor!

8
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:26,100
Hey, what's with you?

9
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:27,267
Don't you want to be here?

10
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:29,567
I told you to take me back
to mommy, didn't I?

11
00:00:29,633 --> 00:00:31,600
Then go home by yourself.

12
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:34,400
Miss!
Mookie!

13
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:41,167
With what I am going to do,
you will learn your lesson.

14
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:43,433
No, Mommy! No!

15
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:44,000
Mommy!

16
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:47,300
Mommy, Mommy...

17
00:00:47,367 --> 00:00:49,733
I heard someone
crying over there.

18
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:52,100
That's Mookie,
Ma'am Olive's daughter.

19
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:53,100
Well, she got scolded,
that's why.

20
00:00:53,167 --> 00:00:56,233
Mommy!

21
00:01:32,067 --> 00:01:33,300
As of now,

22
00:01:33,367 --> 00:01:36,133
there are no documented cases
of MSBP in the Philippines.

23
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:40,033
That's why there's not much
awareness of this disease here.

24
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:43,033
If you want to gain a better
understanding of MSBP,

25
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:45,867
I suggest you watch
a documentary

26
00:01:45,933 --> 00:01:48,500
about a case of MSBP in America.

27
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:51,300
The one about
Gypsy Rose Blanchard.

28
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:53,033
Okay, Doc.

29
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:54,500
Thank you.

30
00:01:54,567 --> 00:01:56,133
Wait, Astrid.

31
00:01:56,200 --> 00:02:01,333
Who is this acquaintance
you're saying might have MSBP?

32
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,900
Why don't you bring her here,

33
00:02:02,967 --> 00:02:04,700
so we can better understand
her situation

34
00:02:04,767 --> 00:02:06,667
and give her appropriate
treatment?

35
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:09,967
We're not that close.

36
00:02:10,033 --> 00:02:12,267
But I'll talk to her
about this.

37
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:13,400
Thank you again.

38
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,433
Maybe you just really
like children, Emma,

39
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:23,733
that's why you were so affected

40
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:26,433
by the screaming
of your boss' daughter.

41
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:31,900
Well whatever you hear or see,
don't interfere.

42
00:02:31,967 --> 00:02:33,233
Just work hard.

43
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:36,100
Who knows, you'll be promoted
to head housekeeper.

44
00:02:36,167 --> 00:02:40,233
I heard that Olive pays
a high salary.

45
00:02:44,067 --> 00:02:45,200
But you know, Emma,

46
00:02:45,267 --> 00:02:47,900
if you're going to have
a hard time, don't continue.

47
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:48,700
What?

48
00:02:49,967 --> 00:02:51,000
What did you say?

49
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:53,367
She just started her work there.

50
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:59,233
You talk as if you can provide
for all the needs of this house.

51
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:01,433
Mother, what's this again?
Is this war again?

52
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:04,467
Of course, I just want
to give Emma a good life.

53
00:03:04,533 --> 00:03:06,367
She doesn't have
to struggle there!

54
00:03:06,433 --> 00:03:08,767
Oh, you see!
What are you getting at?

55
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:10,233
I can do it, I can...

56
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:11,000
- What?
- I can spend for...

57
00:03:11,067 --> 00:03:12,267
What are you trying to say?

58
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:13,700
As long as I earn a lot.

59
00:03:13,767 --> 00:03:14,633
That I am a burden?

60
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:15,667
It's not like that, Mother.

61
00:03:15,733 --> 00:03:17,000
That's what you're saying!

62
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:18,000
I'm not saying anything
- Dan!
- like that.

63
00:03:19,067 --> 00:03:20,200
Dan!

64
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,133
- You're something else, Mother.
- Mother, that's enough.
Let's just eat.

65
00:03:21,967 --> 00:03:23,167
This, the dish is delicious.

66
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:25,067
It's your husband.

67
00:03:25,133 --> 00:03:27,767
The king of spoiling the day!

68
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:29,500
I don't have
an appetite anymore!

69
00:03:29,567 --> 00:03:30,900
No more!

70
00:03:30,967 --> 00:03:33,400
Mother, Mother,
it's not like that.

71
00:03:33,467 --> 00:03:34,133
Dan.

72
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:37,200
Let it go.

73
00:03:37,267 --> 00:03:39,167
Leave it alone.

74
00:03:39,233 --> 00:03:41,333
Your mother is something else.

75
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:43,833
Her remarks can be
annoying sometimes.

76
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:45,200
Our mother.

77
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:46,767
Of course, we're family now.

78
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:51,567
But when she starts nagging,
I just let it enter here

79
00:03:51,633 --> 00:03:54,800
and come out the other side so
the conversation won't be long.

80
00:03:57,233 --> 00:04:00,133
I'm really lucky
with my husband.

81
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,167
You know, you don't have
to think about

82
00:04:05,233 --> 00:04:09,333
giving me a good life
or a luxurious life.

83
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,800
I'm happy here.

84
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:12,600
And it's simple...

85
00:04:13,633 --> 00:04:15,700
as long as we're together.

86
00:04:15,767 --> 00:04:17,467
We have Mother,

87
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:20,467
and if we're lucky,
we'll even be given a child.

88
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:23,733
But, Ems, didn't the doctor say

89
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:26,400
we wouldn't be able
to have another child?

90
00:04:26,467 --> 00:04:30,533
What's with you? Who knows,
we will have a miracle.

91
00:04:30,633 --> 00:04:33,633
Maybe the Lord
will hear my prayer.

92
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:38,400
You know, when that happens,
I won't ask for anything else.

93
00:04:44,233 --> 00:04:45,433
Come on, let's eat.

94
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:46,600
Let's eat.

95
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,100
Emma!

96
00:04:59,167 --> 00:05:01,200
Emma, help me.

97
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:02,233
It's heavy.
Oh, here.

98
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,667
It's heavy.

99
00:05:06,733 --> 00:05:07,867
Is this all I have to wash?

100
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,200
Yes, that's all.

101
00:05:09,267 --> 00:05:11,400
This is the entire laundry area.

102
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:13,100
This is big,
so you can take care of it.

103
00:05:13,167 --> 00:05:16,200
Because Ma'am Olive asked me
to do a lot of things.

104
00:05:16,267 --> 00:05:18,567
Oh my God,
the work doesn't seem to end.

105
00:05:18,633 --> 00:05:20,233
I'm tired of working here.

106
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:22,467
I've been working nonstop
for a while now.

107
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:27,233
I don't know why Ma'am Olive
fired my colleagues.

108
00:05:28,267 --> 00:05:31,033
Good thing the uniform fits you.

109
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,067
Oh, well.

110
00:05:32,133 --> 00:05:33,300
I'm in a hurry.

111
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:34,200
I'll leave you here.
You take care of that.

112
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:35,367
Do you know
what to do with that?

113
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:36,800
- Yes, I'll take care of it.
- Okay, be careful.

114
00:05:58,833 --> 00:06:00,500
Surprise.

115
00:06:16,067 --> 00:06:17,700
But, Mommy...

116
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:20,967
I already have a lot of dolls.

117
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:23,767
Don't you want that?

118
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:27,033
You have a growing collection.

119
00:06:50,533 --> 00:06:51,500
Flor?

120
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,633
Flor?

121
00:06:59,133 --> 00:06:59,967
Flor?

122
00:07:13,667 --> 00:07:14,467
Flor?

123
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,400
Okay, this will be quick.

124
00:07:44,333 --> 00:07:45,300
That's it.

125
00:07:51,767 --> 00:07:53,000
There you go.

126
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:56,600
See, that was fast.

127
00:08:04,933 --> 00:08:07,700
Mommy, what's that for?

128
00:08:07,767 --> 00:08:09,567
Antispasmodic.

129
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:10,800
So, what it does is

130
00:08:10,867 --> 00:08:14,833
it reduces the effects of
your bowel and bladder problems.

131
00:08:14,900 --> 00:08:17,100
Especially
since you have a spinal injury,

132
00:08:17,167 --> 00:08:21,433
so it can relieve your bowel
movements and bladder control.

133
00:08:22,667 --> 00:08:24,433
Why do you ask?

134
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:26,033
Are you skeptical?

135
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:29,900
No. No, Mommy.

136
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:31,467
That's good.

137
00:08:31,533 --> 00:08:34,133
Remember, I'm a doctor.

138
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,767
I know what I'm doing.

139
00:08:41,667 --> 00:08:42,933
Mommy?

140
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:43,967
Yes?

141
00:08:45,767 --> 00:08:51,767
I've learned my lesson
since you locked me up.

142
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:54,033
Promise, Mommy,
I'll behave this time.

143
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:58,833
I won't leave the house anymore,
and I'll listen to you.

144
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:01,400
Just promise me, Mommy,

145
00:09:01,467 --> 00:09:04,900
don't lock me up
in this room again.

146
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:07,733
No.

147
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:13,667
I know you'll just
disobey me again.

148
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:18,833
So up until, you prove to me

149
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:21,667
that you will follow
all my wishes...

150
00:09:22,700 --> 00:09:26,867
only then,
will I let you out of this room.

151
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:27,867
Okay?

152
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:33,733
Mommy!

153
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:36,833
Mommy!

154
00:09:37,967 --> 00:09:40,833
Mommy, please,
I don't want to stay here.

155
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:43,967
I want to go outside,
even if it's just in the garden.

156
00:09:44,033 --> 00:09:48,667
I want to see the birds,
the butterflies, the flowers.

157
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:50,300
Please, Mommy.

158
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:52,600
I'll do everything.

159
00:09:52,667 --> 00:09:56,000
Please, Mommy,
don't deprive me of that!

160
00:09:56,067 --> 00:09:59,333
I said no!

161
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:00,500
Just stay here!

162
00:10:03,567 --> 00:10:04,533
Who's that?

163
00:10:05,867 --> 00:10:07,967
Is there anyone there?

164
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:12,933
Who's there?

165
00:10:15,233 --> 00:10:16,233
Flor?

166
00:10:17,267 --> 00:10:18,167
Flor?

167
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:20,433
Ma'am?

168
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:22,033
Ma'am? Yes, Ma'am?

169
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:23,033
Why?
What is it?

170
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:27,100
I just got the padlock
you asked me to get, Ma'am.

171
00:10:27,167 --> 00:10:28,067
Why?

172
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:30,200
Good.

173
00:10:30,267 --> 00:10:31,667
Go ahead.

174
00:10:31,733 --> 00:10:34,367
Put a double lock
on Mookie's room.

175
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:36,200
A double lock, Ma'am?

176
00:10:36,267 --> 00:10:40,933
- This lock is strong, Ma'am.
- Just do what I say.

177
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:41,900
Okay.

178
00:10:41,967 --> 00:10:45,400
Mookie must not leave the room.

179
00:10:45,467 --> 00:10:47,067
Okay, Ma'am. I'll lock it now.

180
00:10:55,033 --> 00:10:59,167
Mommy, please!
I'm begging you, Mommy!

181
00:10:59,233 --> 00:11:02,133
Please let me go outside!

182
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,900
Mommy!

183
00:11:05,967 --> 00:11:07,700
Mommy!

184
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:10,600
Mommy!

185
00:11:10,667 --> 00:11:14,700
Mommy, please!
I'm begging you, Mommy!

186
00:11:14,767 --> 00:11:17,533
No! Just stay there!

187
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:20,900
And I'll tell you
when you can go out.

188
00:11:20,967 --> 00:11:26,633
Mommy! Didn't you say
you'd do anything for me?

189
00:11:27,933 --> 00:11:30,667
Mommy, didn't you say
you wouldn't hurt me?

190
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:33,667
Why do you lie to me, Mommy?

191
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:42,900
Mommy, please!

192
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,667
Mommy!

193
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:49,600
Please, Mommy!

194
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:53,233
Please, Mommy, I'm begging you.
Please, I'll behave this time.

195
00:11:53,300 --> 00:11:58,533
Just let me out of my room,
Mommy!

196
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:01,733
Mommy!

197
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:08,400
Mommy!

198
00:12:12,033 --> 00:12:13,533
I pity her.

199
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:17,567
Mommy, I want to go outside!

200
00:12:17,633 --> 00:12:19,967
Mommy...

201
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:25,700
Mommy, please.

202
00:12:25,767 --> 00:12:28,367
Mommy...

203
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:40,167
Hello?

204
00:12:40,233 --> 00:12:42,133
Oh, aren't you busy?

205
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,933
Is it bad to ask how my wife is?

206
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,767
What's with you?
I have a lot of laundry to do.

207
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:50,533
Emma, let's go on a date.

208
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:52,433
You know, I just got my salary.

209
00:12:53,467 --> 00:12:54,933
Let's go out.

210
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:58,700
Well, isn't our rent
still not enough?

211
00:12:58,767 --> 00:13:01,067
What if Ms. Tina
asks for payment?

212
00:13:01,133 --> 00:13:03,833
Besides, we have a lot of
expenses so let's not go out.

213
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:04,700
What's with you?

214
00:13:04,767 --> 00:13:06,700
It's just a simple
fishball date.

215
00:13:06,767 --> 00:13:09,200
It won't be used up right away.

216
00:13:09,267 --> 00:13:10,100
Oh, okay.

217
00:13:10,167 --> 00:13:11,800
Let's see each other later,
okay?

218
00:13:11,867 --> 00:13:12,867
Love you.

219
00:13:12,933 --> 00:13:14,633
I love you more, Emma.

220
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:15,867
Okay.

221
00:13:15,933 --> 00:13:17,733
Don't tire yourself too much.

222
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:18,600
Okay.

223
00:13:20,267 --> 00:13:21,000
Bye.

224
00:13:32,633 --> 00:13:34,867
Love, why are you so quiet?

225
00:13:34,933 --> 00:13:36,633
I thought you wanted to date me?

226
00:13:37,767 --> 00:13:41,533
Oh, Emma. The thing I told you
about the fishball...

227
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:44,467
I was just joking.

228
00:13:46,333 --> 00:13:49,600
But this is where we ended up.

229
00:13:49,667 --> 00:13:50,933
That's fine.

230
00:13:52,233 --> 00:13:54,333
Why? Is there a problem?

231
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:57,633
I hit a car, Emma.

232
00:13:59,533 --> 00:14:01,500
My salary is gone.

233
00:14:01,567 --> 00:14:03,367
I'm even in debt.

234
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:07,833
This damn life,
I'm working hard already.

235
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:11,433
But no matter how hard I try,
I'm still unlucky.

236
00:14:12,833 --> 00:14:14,000
Dan, that's okay.

237
00:14:15,067 --> 00:14:16,733
What's important is, look...

238
00:14:17,767 --> 00:14:19,633
nothing bad happened to you.

239
00:14:20,933 --> 00:14:22,333
Every 15th and 30th,

240
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:24,100
I'll get my salary
from Ma'am Olive.

241
00:14:25,167 --> 00:14:27,100
Don't think negatively.

242
00:14:27,167 --> 00:14:28,933
I'll take care
of the food first.

243
00:14:30,967 --> 00:14:36,400
Then, I'll ask Ms. Tina
to give us an extension.

244
00:14:36,467 --> 00:14:37,333
I'm embarrassed.

245
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:39,200
I can't give you
a good life anymore,

246
00:14:39,267 --> 00:14:43,567
and then I'm giving you
this problem.

247
00:14:45,567 --> 00:14:49,500
Why? Didn't I give you
a problem before?

248
00:14:49,567 --> 00:14:51,867
I've been depressed
for a long time, haven't I?

249
00:14:51,933 --> 00:14:53,733
But you didn't leave me.

250
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:55,967
You always put up with me.

251
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:00,467
And no relationship
doesn't go through trials.

252
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:06,433
The important thing is that our
bond with each other is strong.

253
00:15:09,667 --> 00:15:11,233
Don't be sad anymore.

254
00:15:12,967 --> 00:15:16,833
Did you forget that we first met
at the fishball stall?

255
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:19,367
Remember?

256
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,833
This is okay.

257
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:25,400
Okay, let's eat.

258
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,333
Will I be like this forever?

259
00:15:39,367 --> 00:15:40,800
If it's always like this,

260
00:15:40,867 --> 00:15:44,000
I wish I was born into
a different family.

261
00:15:44,067 --> 00:15:46,500
I wish my mommy was different.

262
00:15:46,567 --> 00:15:49,733
I don't want this anymore!
I don't want it anymore.

263
00:15:58,167 --> 00:16:01,133
Mommy? Mommy, is that you?

264
00:16:02,167 --> 00:16:04,667
Mommy, will you let me out?

265
00:16:06,133 --> 00:16:07,133
Mommy?

266
00:16:09,067 --> 00:16:12,200
Mommy, will you let me out?

267
00:16:12,267 --> 00:16:13,200
Mommy?

268
00:16:13,267 --> 00:16:14,467
Mookie?

269
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:20,600
Oh, Mookie,
I didn't get your dirty clothes.

270
00:16:20,667 --> 00:16:21,933
Let me get them, okay?

271
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:33,567
I'll go out now, okay?

272
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:39,900
Oh my, how many days have you
been wearing that sweater?

273
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:42,200
Give me that. Let's take it off
to wash it, okay?

274
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:46,367
Are you okay?

275
00:16:46,433 --> 00:16:48,700
All right. I'll go out now.

276
00:16:51,067 --> 00:16:52,500
Flor.

277
00:16:52,567 --> 00:16:54,933
What?

278
00:16:55,000 --> 00:17:00,533
Maybe you can ask mommy?

279
00:17:03,767 --> 00:17:06,533
Flor, I don't want to be
locked up here anymore.

280
00:17:07,733 --> 00:17:12,533
If only I could do
the things I used to do,

281
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:14,400
I'd be okay with that.

282
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,167
Please, Flor.

283
00:17:16,233 --> 00:17:17,900
Oh, Mookie.

284
00:17:19,467 --> 00:17:25,700
I'm sorry, but, you know,
when it comes to your mommy,

285
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:28,500
my mouth is zipped shut.

286
00:17:28,567 --> 00:17:30,667
I hope you understand, Mookie.

287
00:17:30,733 --> 00:17:35,233
I have a family to support,
I can't be fired.

288
00:17:36,300 --> 00:17:37,600
I'm sorry.

289
00:17:38,833 --> 00:17:40,200
I'll just go down.

290
00:18:19,967 --> 00:18:22,600
Will I be like this forever?

291
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:25,133
If it's always like this,

292
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:28,500
I wish I was born
into a different family.

293
00:18:28,567 --> 00:18:31,167
I wish my mommy was different.

294
00:18:31,233 --> 00:18:33,467
I don't want this anymore.

295
00:18:33,533 --> 00:18:34,767
I don't want it anymore.

296
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:39,833
I wish I could be like
a bird that can fly.

297
00:18:45,633 --> 00:18:47,600
This is hers.

298
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:49,000
This belongs to Mookie.

299
00:18:55,067 --> 00:18:59,033
But no,
there's nothing I can do.

300
00:18:59,100 --> 00:19:00,367
Help me.

301
00:19:00,433 --> 00:19:01,900
I can't do this anymore.

302
00:19:05,433 --> 00:19:06,333
Oh my God.

303
00:19:07,467 --> 00:19:09,667
She might do something bad.

304
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:11,933
No, she can't.

305
00:19:38,933 --> 00:19:39,767
Mommy.

306
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:43,033
Mommy? Mommy.

307
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:49,167
Mommy.

308
00:19:49,233 --> 00:19:51,567
Mommy...

309
00:19:58,133 --> 00:19:59,067
Mookie?

310
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:01,467
Mookie?

311
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:02,933
Mommy?

312
00:20:12,767 --> 00:20:14,133
- Mookie.
- Mommy!

313
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,400
Mommy!

314
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:30,067
Mommy!

315
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:19,967
Whatever you're thinking
and feeling,

316
00:21:20,033 --> 00:21:23,633
I hope you won't forget
that there are other people

317
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:27,800
who will listen to you
and understand you.

318
00:21:27,867 --> 00:21:32,400
We haven't met yet,
but believe it or not,

319
00:21:32,467 --> 00:21:35,500
I feel the pain you're feeling.

320
00:21:35,567 --> 00:21:38,000
So be strong, Mookie.

321
00:21:38,067 --> 00:21:39,400
I'm here.

322
00:21:39,467 --> 00:21:41,900
I'm ready to listen
to what you have to say.

323
00:22:22,467 --> 00:22:24,033
And who are you?

324
00:22:30,733 --> 00:22:33,567
Why doesn't your boss
let his daughter out?

325
00:22:33,633 --> 00:22:34,900
Is Olive grumpy?

326
00:22:34,967 --> 00:22:37,600
Yes. And what is her
daughter's disease?

327
00:22:37,667 --> 00:22:40,900
Flor, do we have a new helper?

328
00:22:40,967 --> 00:22:43,567
I think I heard a new voice.

329
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:45,133
Yes, that's Emma.

330
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,633
Our new laundrywoman.

331
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:49,067
Here's the medicine
you're asking for.

332
00:22:49,167 --> 00:22:50,400
Thank you, Astrid.

333
00:22:50,467 --> 00:22:52,333
Olive, does Mookie
really need that?

334
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,300
Those are steroids.

335
00:22:53,367 --> 00:22:55,900
When the dose is higher,
the effects are bad.

336
00:22:55,967 --> 00:22:58,200
Is Emma still there?

337
00:22:58,267 --> 00:23:00,567
Yes, but she's just
finishing ironing.

338
00:23:00,633 --> 00:23:02,133
She'll be going home in a while.

339
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:03,433
Why did you ask?

340
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:05,533
I want to see Emma.

341
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:06,700
Madam Beautiful.

342
00:23:06,767 --> 00:23:07,500
Who are you?

343
00:23:07,567 --> 00:23:10,300
You must be Madam Olive.
